In general, because of poor survivability of these coronaviruses on surfaces, there is likely very low risk of spread from products or packaging that are shipped over a period of days or weeks at ambient temperatures. Coronaviruses are generally thought to be spread most often by respiratory droplets. Currently there is no evidence to support transmission of COVID-19 associated with imported goods and there have not been any cases of COVID-19 in the United States associated with imported goods. Information will be provided on the Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) website as it becomes available.

Sellers are not required to provide a reference price, but if they do, it should be (a) the Manufacturer's Suggested Retail Price (MSRP) or similar List Price of the product; or (b) the price at which the item has been recently offered for sale and for a reasonable period of time.

Salam,\n\nWish məhsulunuz (məhsullarınız.source_string:
Hello,

Wish has received the enclosed California Proposition 65 notice regarding your product(s). A California Proposition 65 violation can constitute a violation of Wish’s Terms of Use (see sec. 5 para. 6) and Wish policies; see, e.g.: Wish Merchant Policy 7.20.

What is Proposition 65?

Proposition 65 is a ballot initiative passed by California voters in 1986, is a toxic chemicals right-to-know law requiring a company doing business in California to place warnings on products and, if the product is sold on the internet, on web pages featuring the product.  The law requires the warning when certain chemicals in the products are present in levels that could cause certain levels of exposure to the consumer. 

The law allows private enforcers to bring notices of violation of any of 950 chemicals it regulates, which in turn requires the company, as one option, to add warnings that the product at issue contains specific chemicals that can cause cancer or reproductive harm.  Another option is to withdraw the product from California sale. Neither option exempts the company from liability for the period of time the product was sold to California consumers without a warning.  The warning must be both on the product packaging and on the Wish web page where the product is featured.

Actions Taken by Wish

In response to this report, Wish has reviewed the applicable listing(s) for non-compliance and the following product listing(s) was removed from the platform in all applicable jurisdictions:

Wish-də müştərilər bizim üçün birinci də.source_string:
At Wish, we put customers first and are willing to pay to insure that Wish users receive excellent service. Today, we learned that one of your orders was not prepared in accordance with Postnord rules, so we have automatically refunded you for your purchase!

Sometimes, merchants have already shipped your package. If this is the case, you may receive a message from Postnord to pay VAT and the handling fee. Since you have already been refunded, you will have two options:

1. If you don't want your item, then do nothing & ignore the messages. OR.
2. If you do want your item, contact Postnord with your order ID and they will release the package free of charge. That means we’ve covered your whole purchase, shipping fees & Postnord VAT for you!

We apologize for any inconvenience and are working round the clock to make sure all 1 million merchants follow Postnord rules in the future!

{%1=app name} istifadəçilərin məlumat şə.source_string: {%1=app name} is constantly looking for ways to gather and present information about merchants and their items to help users make informed choices. In {%1=app name}'s Premier Merchant Program, merchant performance across a variety of metrics is tracked in an automated way, and if it meets or exceeds certain thresholds, merchants are eligible for the Premier badge. User ratings of the merchant and the merchant's items, refunds, fulfillment, and compliance with {%1=app name} policies are some of the more notable groups of elements that are tracked. When {%1=app name} shows the badge and a brief description, we may highlight a few areas that reflect merchant performance in specific categories such as item quality, fulfillment & shipping, and customer satisfaction. The formula or approach for monitoring and reporting on merchant performance, including performance areas and minimum scores, may be updated over time.

{%1=app name} pul müqabilində məlumatlar.source_string: {%1=app name} does not sell your data for money. {%1=app name} does share data about app activity, such as purchases, with companies and service providers in the advertising ecosystem in ways that may be considered a sale under CCPA. The shared data is associated with a number such as an Ad ID, not your name. If you wish to opt-out of such sharing toggle the appropriate selector to "off"

{%1=app name} siyasətləri əqli mülkiyyət.source_string: {%1=app name} policies prohibit the misuse of intellectual property. When {%1=app name} is provided evidence that a branded product violates its intellectual property rights, {%1=app name} responds to such concerns on an expedited basis.
